size:
Brand New, Factory Sealed, Complete Warranty 



The Chronoscope collection has taken the legendary Speedmaster design and combined it with inspiration from OMEGA’s chronograph wristwatches from the 1940s.




This 43 mm model is crafted in stainless steel with a blue dial with silvery subdials. Along with a blue anodized aluminium bezel ring with its tachymeter scale, the leaf-shaped hands and Arabic numerals are rhodium-plated, with a unique “spiral” track pattern running beneath the numbers.




Most notably, the dial is printed with three distinctive timing scales in a 1940’s “snail” design, including a tachymeter scale, a pulsometer scale and a telemeter scale.




Presented on a stainless steel bracelet, the watch features a silvery small-seconds counter at 9H, and a silvery 60-minute and 12-hour recorder at 3H. Inside, the timepiece is driven by the OMEGA Co-Axial Master Chronometer Calibre 9908.




Anti-magnetic




The movement is unaffected by exposure to strong magnetic fields, even those greater than 1.5 tesla (15,000 gauss).


Chronograph




The chronograph function is a mechanism for measuring time intervals. A chronograph watch can therefore be used to time events while displaying the time like any traditional watch.


Chronometer




Label given to a watch which has undergone precision tests and received a certificate from an official body (COSC).


Master Chronometer Certified




Guaranteeing the Swiss industry’s highest standard of precision, performance and magnetic-resistance, as set by the Swiss Federal Institute of Metrology (METAS).


Pulsometer




A watch with a scale to measure the number of heartbeats per minute.


Small seconds




A hand on a sub-dial which tracks seconds typically it completes a full rotation in one minute.


Tachymeter




A tachymeter watch has a function for measuring speed. It is a chronograph with a graduated dial on which speed can be read in kilometres per hour based on a 1000 metre distance.


Telemeter




This precision tool can measure exactly how far you are from something that is visible and audible, such as your distance from a lightening storm.


Time zone function




Allows the hour hand to be easily adjusted to different time zones without stopping the watch.


Transparent case back




A transparent case back - frequently made of sapphire - makes it possible to see the movement inside the watch.


TECHNICAL DATA

Bracelet: steel


Case: Steel


Case diameter: 43 mm


Dial color: Blue


Crystal: Scratch‑resistant sapphire crystal with anti‑reflective treatment on both sides


Water resistance: 5 bar (50 metres / 167 feet)

ABOUT


This pre-owned 2022 Tag Heuer Formula 1 x Indy 500 Limited Edition CAZ101AR is in like new condition. The watch comes as a full set and is still in warranty with Tag Heuer until 2024, with additional 1 year warranty from The Watch Village from date of purchase.




All of our watches undergo a thorough inspection of accuracy, functionality and condition to meet our strict standards. Additionally, we check each watch against records to ensure authenticity and ownership status.




This limited edition timepiece was created in a quantity of 500 pieces to celebrate Tag Heuer’s long standing partnership with the Indy 500 and was produced exclusively for the race. The watch is completely centred around the Indy 500 theming, with the base of the dial featuring an exclusive black grained effect to represent the texture of the racetrack. In addition, the chapter ring of the dial is coloured in red to honour the Indy’s iconic brickwork start/finish line, as well as being a nod towards the Indy’s “Brickyard” nickname. Gold accents can also be seen throughout the dial as a representation of the Indy’s logo, as well as the appearance of the famous Pagoda Tower that houses the race printed on the chronograph sub-dial. The dial is surrounded by a black tachymetre bezel whereby the “tachymetre” wording has been replaced with “INDY 500”.Of which is sat upon a 43mm stainless steel case, which is fitted to a stainless steel bracelet. All powered by a quartz precision movement.
